</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2F7A7747DBF5EFFDCB2C3643603933DE" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="62756B6C78AA6B2EB94FD2FF52F69CC5" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF9F3522FD2EB9FF2E6BE9344B3576D0" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">
Inhabits coral reef areas (
<bibRefCitation id="9844F172B82A552EB85C3533EFED613B" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1042.64474" author="Mehrotra, R" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" pagination="73 - 188" refId="B42" refString="Mehrotra, R, Caballer Gutierrez, MA, Scott, CM, Arnold, S, Monchanin, C, Viyakarn, V, Chavanich, C, 2021. An updated inventory of sea slugs from Koh Tao, Thailand, with notes on their ecology and a dramatic biodiversity increase for Thai waters. ZooKeys 1042: 73 - 188, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1042.64474" title="An updated inventory of sea slugs from Koh Tao, Thailand, with notes on their ecology and a dramatic biodiversity increase for Thai waters." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1042.64474" volume="1042" year="2021">Mehrotra et al. 2021</bibRefCitation>
). Feeds on hydroids (
<bibRefCitation id="17C7FAE3C959AA9BD64B61C58152BF13" author="Yonow, N" journalOrPublisher="Pensoft Publications, Sofia / Moscow" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" refId="B68" refString="Yonow, N, 2008. Sea Slugs of the Red Sea. Pensoft Publications, Sofia/Moscow" title="Sea Slugs of the Red Sea." year="2008">Yonow 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="E74974DC2562A23588A9CC29031180BC" author="Gosliner, TM" journalOrPublisher="Jacksonville, Florida" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" refId="B30" refString="Gosliner, TM, Valdes, A, Behrens, DW, 2015. Nudibranch and sea slug identification, Indo-Pacific. New World Publications, Inc. Jacksonville, Florida" title="Nudibranch and sea slug identification, Indo-Pacific. New World Publications, Inc." year="2015">Gosliner et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
). A new record to Kuwait and the APG.
</paragraph>
